column2: Analysis of gene expression differences in lymph node B cell populations of HIV-infected and uninfected controls
This study examines the gene expression profiles of resident lymph node B cell populations in HIV-infected and uninfected controls.
8 different B cell subsets were sorted from lymph nodes of HIV-uninfected and infected individuals and compared by RNA-seq
Expression profiling by high throughput sequencing
